{% block title %}
    6. Mobilize New Units
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="alert alert-info">
        Move the newly purchased units from the mobilization zone on the game board to eligible spaces you have controlled
        <strong>since the start of your turn</strong>
    </div>
    <div class="alert alert-info">
        If for some reason you cannot place all purchased units, you choose which ones to put back and get your IPCs refunded
    </div>
    <div class="alert alert-danger">
        You canâ€™t use industrial complexes that you captured or purchased this turn or that are owned by a friendly power.
    </div>
    <h5>Production Limit</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Major Industrial Complex: </strong>10 units (-1 per damage)
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Minor Industrial Complex: </strong>3 Units (-1 per damage)
        </li>
        <li>If you purchased more units than you can mobilize, you must return the over-produced units to the box and the cost of the units is reimbursed to you.</li>
    </ul>
    <h5>Placement Rules</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Land Units and Strategic Bombers</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Only in territories containing eligible industrial complexes</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Sea Units</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Only in sea zones (even hostile ones) adjacent to territories containing eligible industrial complexes</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Fighters and Tactical Bombers</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    in territories containing an eligible industrial complex
                </li>
                <li>
                    in sea zones containing an aircraft carrier owned by your power (even a newly purchased one) in a sea zone (even a hostile one) adjacent to a territory containing an eligible industrial complex
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Facilities</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Major Industrial Complexes:</strong> only in originally controlled territories with an IPC value of 3 or higher, but not on Islands
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Minor Industrial Complexes:</strong> only in territories with an IPC value of 2 or higher, but not on Islands
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Air Base:</strong> in any controlled territory
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Naval Base:</strong> in any controlled territory with a coastline
                </li>
                <li><div class="alert alert-danger">You can't have more than one facility of the same type per territory</div></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
{% endblock %}